item.title: 2024 National K-12: Does a Higher Rating Lead to a Higher Standing?
item.description: Statistics of 2024 National K-12 Grades Championship Fourth grade (age 9) is the most competitive, with nearly 350 participants. Grades 3, 4, and 5 have the highest number of participants, while Grade K has the fewest. 11th Grade boasts the highest average rating of 1,600. The mean is indicated by the red bar in the plot below, while the black bars in the boxplot represent the median. Does a higher rating guarantee a higher standing?
